<body>

<header>
    <h1>The Strategy of Sovereignty</h1>
    <p>Dissecting Geopolitics Beyond the Hysteria</p>
</header>

<div class="container">
    <section>
        <h2>EDCA, War, and the Instant Analyst</h2>
        <p>There’s a new fear-mongering script doing the rounds. The chain messages have officially leveled up. It used to be that if you didn’t forward a message to ten people, you’d just have bad luck in love. Now, the people who spam the family group chat have suddenly transformed into "geopolitical experts."</p>

        <div class="highlight-box">
            "The US and Israel hit Iran. Iran retaliated against countries housing US bases. The Philippines has EDCA sites. Therefore, we’re all going to be turned into ash by tomorrow."
        </div>

        <p>What do we call this? <strong>Fear mongering</strong>. A <strong>slippery slope</strong>. It takes the absolute worst-case scenario and sells it to you as a "guaranteed event." Once you’re paralyzed by fear, you stop analyzing. You just react.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <div class="fact-card">
            <h3>1. The EDCA Reality Check</h3>
            <p>The Enhanced Defense Cooperation Agreement (EDCA) is not a return to permanent US bases. We haven't surrendered our sovereignty. These are still Philippine military bases. The setup is "rotational presence"—access, logistics, and storage for gear.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fact-card">
            <h3>2. Presence ≠ Automatic Target</h3>
            <p>If the logic "US presence = instant target" were true, Japan, South Korea, Germany, and Italy would have been wiped off the map decades ago. Nations are strategic; they don't waste multi-billion dollar missiles on nations without direct skin in the game.</p>
        </div>
        
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Fact vs. Fiction Table</h3>
        <table class="comparison-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Fiction / Fear-Mongering</th>
                    <th>Geopolitical Fact</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td class="fiction-cell">EDCA means permanent US bases.</td>
                    <td class="fact-cell">Sites remain PH property; presence is rotational.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="fiction-cell">We are an automatic nuclear target.</td>
                    <td class="fact-cell">Strategic calculus prioritizes active combatants, not logistics sites.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="fiction-cell">Neutrality ensures total safety.</td>
                    <td class="fact-cell">Unarmed neutrality often leads to territorial loss.</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </section>

    <section id="share">
        <h3 style="text-align: center;">Share this Strategy</h3>
        <div class="share-bar">
            <button class="share-btn fb" onclick="shareFB()">Facebook</button>
            <button class="share-btn x-com" onclick="shareX()">X (Twitter)</button>
            <button class="share-btn li" onclick="shareLI()">LinkedIn</button>
            <button class="share-btn copy-url" onclick="copyLink()">Copy Link</button>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="author-sig">— Glenn Junsay Pansensoy</div>

    <div class="disclaimer-box" style="background: #000; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Feel free to share or repost. Do not edit the content and ensure you credit the author. Keep the name of <strong>Glenn Junsay Pansensoy</strong> attached. Decency is free.
    </div>

    <section id="comment-section">
        <h3>Discussion</h3>
        <form id="comment-form">
            <input type="text" id="username" placeholder="Your Name" required>
            <textarea id="comment-text" rows="4" placeholder="Share your thoughts..." required></textarea>
            <button type="submit">Post Comment</button>
        </form>
        <div id="comments" class="comment-list"></div>
    </section>
</div>

<footer>
    <p>&copy; 2026 | Strategic Awareness Project</p>
</footer>

<script>
    const articleUrl = window.location.href;
    const articleTitle = "The Strategy of Sovereignty - Glenn Junsay Pansensoy";

    function shareFB() { window.open(`https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=${encodeURIComponent(articleUrl)}`, '_blank'); }
    function shareX() { window.open(`https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=${encodeURIComponent(articleUrl)}&text=${encodeURIComponent(articleTitle)}`, '_blank'); }
    function shareLI() { window.open(`https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=${encodeURIComponent(articleUrl)}`, '_blank'); }
    
    function copyLink() {
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(articleUrl);
        alert("Link copied to clipboard!");
    }

    const commentForm = document.getElementById('comment-form');
    const commentList = document.getElementById('comments');

    window.onload = () => {
        const saved = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('glenn_comments')) || [];
        saved.forEach(c => renderComment(c.user, c.text));
    };

    commentForm.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        const user = document.getElementById('username').value;
        const text = document.getElementById('comment-text').value;
        renderComment(user, text);
        const saved = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('glenn_comments')) || [];
        saved.push({ user, text });
        localStorage.setItem('glenn_comments', JSON.stringify(saved));
        commentForm.reset();
    });

    function renderComment(user, text) {
        const div = document.createElement('div');
        div.className = 'comment-item';
        div.innerHTML = `<div class="comment-author">${user}</div><div>${text}</div>`;
        commentList.prepend(div);
    }
</script>
</body>
